         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] therefore, ([you who] always honour meditation, and are concentrated)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] and zealous, and see the end of birth and old age</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (may you) reach the other shore (of birth and death) [TB] may you (reach the other shore of birth and death)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (desire, I know) your root</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>289</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] I will (not) imagine (you)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (from desires) arises fear [TB] from desires (arises fear)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] there is (no) grief, let alone (fear)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] for those who are freed from pleasures</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels">See in particular <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-pkas1a"/>, for b3 also <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-ioltoch716"/>. <bibl><title corresp="ref:chakravarti1930"/><citedRange>17-20</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>111-112</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>17</citedRange></bibl></note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">Uv.1.42a <hi>tasmāt sadā dhyānaratāḥ samāhitā</hi></note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.1.42b <hi>hy ātāpino jātijarāntadarśinaḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">Uv.1.42d <hi>bhaveta jātīmaraṇasya pāragāḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">Uv.2.1a <hi>kāma jānāmi te mūlam</hi></note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">Uv.2.1c <hi>na tvāṃ saṃkalpayiṣyāmi</hi></note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">Uv.2.2b <hi>kāmebhyo jāyate bhayam</hi></note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">Uv.2.2d <hi>nāsti śokaḥ kuto bhayam</hi></note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">Uv.2.03c <hi>ratibhyo vipramuktānām</hi></note></p>
